---
/**
 * bloom-0001 · Figure 1 — "k hashes, one bit array".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/bloom-filters/lessons/0001-what-is-a-bloom-filter.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size,
 * stroke-width, marker-end, …) and self-referential ids. In an .astro file the
 * SVG is plain HTML, so it renders byte-for-byte. SVG ids (ah, r1) are kept as-is
 * to match the source DOM and the #s1 footnote anchors.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        viewBox="0 0 600 260"
        font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="ah"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0 0L10 5L0 10z" fill="#136f63"></path>
            </marker>
        </defs>
        <rect x="0" y="0" width="600" height="260" fill="#fffff8"></rect>
        <rect x="16" y="36" width="118" height="40" rx="6" fill="#e8f1ef" stroke="#136f63"></rect>
        <text x="75" y="61" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#0f4f47">add("apple")</text>
        <text x="75" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#6b675f">k = 3 hashes</text>
        <text x="75" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#6b675f">h1 h2 h3</text>
        <g font-size="13" text-anchor="middle">
            <rect x="180" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect><text
                x="196"
                y="62"
                fill="#9a958a">0</text
            >
            <rect x="214" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#136f63" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect><text
                x="230"
                y="62"
                fill="#fff">1</text
            >
            <rect x="248" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect><text
                x="264"
                y="62"
                fill="#9a958a">0</text
            >
            <rect x="282" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect><text
                x="298"
                y="62"
                fill="#9a958a">0</text
            >
            <rect x="316" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect><text
                x="332"
                y="62"
                fill="#9a958a">0</text
            >
            <rect x="350" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect><text
                x="366"
                y="62"
                fill="#9a958a">0</text
            >
            <rect x="384" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#136f63" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect><text
                x="400"
                y="62"
                fill="#fff">1</text
            >
            <rect x="418" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect><text
                x="434"
                y="62"
                fill="#9a958a">0</text
            >
            <rect x="452" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect><text
                x="468"
                y="62"
                fill="#9a958a">0</text
            >
            <rect x="486" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#136f63" stroke="#0f4f47"></rect><text
                x="502"
                y="62"
                fill="#fff">1</text
            >
            <rect x="520" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect><text
                x="536"
                y="62"
                fill="#9a958a">0</text
            >
            <rect x="554" y="40" width="32" height="32" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect><text
                x="570"
                y="62"
                fill="#9a958a">0</text
            >
        </g>
        <text x="384" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#6b675f"
            >m-bit array — insert sets the k bits the hashes point to</text
        >
        <path
            d="M134 52 L228 56"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#136f63"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            marker-end="url(#ah)"></path>
        <path
            d="M134 56 L398 56"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#136f63"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            marker-end="url(#ah)"></path>
        <path
            d="M134 60 L500 56"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#136f63"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            marker-end="url(#ah)"></path>
        <line x1="16" y1="140" x2="584" y2="140" stroke="#d8d4c8"></line>
        <text x="16" y="168" font-size="14" fill="#111110">query(z): any checked bit = 0 ?</text>
        <rect x="350" y="150" width="234" height="30" rx="6" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="467" y="170" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >YES &#8594; definitely NOT in set</text
        >
        <text x="16" y="216" font-size="14" fill="#111110">query(z): all checked bits = 1 ?</text>
        <rect x="350" y="198" width="234" height="30" rx="6" fill="#fbf3e6" stroke="#9a7a17"></rect>
        <text x="467" y="218" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#7a5e12"
            >PROBABLY &#8594; maybe present, verify</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The filter stores no keys &#8212; just one <code>m</code>-bit array. Insert sets k bits; a
        query checks those k bits, and only one answer is certain.<sup
            ><a href="#s1" id="r1">1</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
